### F1 Store Order API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/order
@userId = 1
@orderId = 1
@orderNumber = ORD-20250824132123-1

### Get all orders (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Get order by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Get order by order number
GET {{baseUrl}}/number/{{orderNumber}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by user ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/Pending
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by status - Processing
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/Processing
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by status - Shipped
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/Shipped
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by status - Delivered
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/Delivered
Content-Type: application/json

### Get orders by status - Cancelled
GET {{baseUrl}}/status/Cancelled
Content-Type: application/json

### Update order status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Processing"
}

### Update order status to Shipped
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Shipped"
}

### Update order status to Delivered
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Delivered"
}

### Update order status to Cancelled
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Cancelled"
}

### Get total revenue (Admin analytics)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/revenue
Content-Type: application/json

### Get total orders count (Admin analytics)
GET {{baseUrl}}/analytics/count
Content-Type: application/json

### Delete order (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{orderId}}
Content-Type: application/json

